From: Lijo Lazar <lijo.lazar@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 7 Aug 2024 21:41:59 +0530
Subject: drm/amdkfd: Add node_id to location_id generically
Git-commit: 42b3a6f12aa56dcf789464d29fdf11f33bf0e793
Patch-mainline: v6.12-rc1
References: jsc#PED-9898 jsc#PED-10191 jsc#PED-10197 jsc#PED-10226 jsc#PED-10237 jsc#PED-10340 jsc#PED-10852 jsc#PED-11022

If there are multiple nodes per kfd device, add nodeid to location_id to
differentiate.

Signed-off-by: Lijo Lazar <lijo.lazar@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Hawking Zhang <Hawking.Zhang@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Acked-by: Patrik Jakobsson <pjakobsson@suse.de>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_topology.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_topology.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_topology.c
index eeff9dadfcb1..fb7a3a846d74 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_topology.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdkfd/kfd_topology.c
@@ -2078,7 +2078,7 @@ int kfd_topology_add_device(struct kfd_node *gpu)
 			HSA_CAP_ASIC_REVISION_MASK);
 
 	dev->node_props.location_id = pci_dev_id(gpu->adev->pdev);
-	if (KFD_GC_VERSION(dev->gpu->kfd) == IP_VERSION(9, 4, 3))
+	if (gpu->kfd->num_nodes > 1)
 		dev->node_props.location_id |= dev->gpu->node_id;
 
 	dev->node_props.domain = pci_domain_nr(gpu->adev->pdev->bus);
